{
  "id": "019d286a-f2d7-7750-81b8-10837072060f",
  "content": "# M4.5: Toggleable CUDA Support for corvia-workspace\n\n## Problem\n\n`corvia-inference` runs ONNX embedding inference on CPU. Users with NVIDIA GPUs get no acceleration. The devcontainer has no GPU awareness. CUDA setup should be optional and toggleable, matching the existing `corvia-workspace enable/disable` pattern for Ollama and SurrealDB.\n\n\n## Approach: Script-Only Toggle\n\nExtend `corvia-workspace.sh` with a `cuda` service. No Dockerfile changes. CUDA toolkit installed at enable-time, CUDA-enabled binary downloaded from GitHub releases.\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-04-m4.5-cuda-toggle-design.md",
